WEBVTT

02:58.500 --> 03:00.860
Excuse me.

03:03.370 --> 03:06.490
Come on, honey, let's
get you ready for bed.

03:18.950 --> 03:21.040
I am no one special,

03:21.080 --> 03:24.020
just a common man
with common thoughts.

03:24.050 --> 03:26.320
I've led a common life.

03:26.360 --> 03:28.260
There are no monuments
dedicated to me.

03:28.290 --> 03:31.390
And my name
will soon be forgotten.

03:31.430 --> 03:33.230
But in one respect,

03:33.260 --> 03:36.790
I've succeeded as gloriously
as anyone who ever lived.

03:36.830 --> 03:38.930
- Looking good, Duke.
- Feeling good.

03:38.970 --> 03:40.730
I've loved another
with all my heart

03:40.770 --> 03:44.800
and soul and for me
that has always been enough.

03:44.840 --> 03:46.240
How's it hanging, Harry?

03:46.280 --> 03:48.970
I keep trying to die,
but they won't let me.

03:49.010 --> 03:51.040
Well, you can't
have everything.

03:54.220 --> 03:55.450
Big day today.

03:55.490 --> 03:58.180
You say that every day,
you old devil.

03:59.560 --> 04:01.520
It's a lovely day
outside.

04:01.560 --> 04:03.790
Let's take a walk.

04:03.830 --> 04:04.890
I don't think so.

04:04.930 --> 04:07.230
Well, we've got to get
you out of this room.

04:07.260 --> 04:08.860
Come on now, honey.
Some fresh air

04:08.900 --> 04:11.330
- would do you good.
- Hello.

04:13.140 --> 04:15.600
I'm sorry,
it's not a good day.

04:15.640 --> 04:17.610
I don't think
she's up for anything.

04:17.640 --> 04:18.800
Hello?

04:20.640 --> 04:24.640
This is Duke,
he's come to read to you.

04:24.680 --> 04:26.950
- Read?
- Mm-hmm.

04:28.180 --> 04:31.020
No.
I don't know.

04:31.050 --> 04:35.120
Oh, come on,
you'll like him, he's very funny.

04:46.840 --> 04:48.170
Ahh...

04:49.610 --> 04:53.540
All right now,
where did we leave off?

04:53.580 --> 04:56.910
Oh, yeah, yeah,
it was the night of the carnival.

04:56.950 --> 05:00.080
"Noah, was there with his friends,
Fin and Sarah."

05:00.120 --> 05:03.310
- Noah?
- That's where they met...

05:03.350 --> 05:05.450
June 6th, 1940.

05:06.890 --> 05:08.790
Allie was
17 years old.

05:09.330 --> 05:11.560
- Little man wins a prize.
- Damn!

05:11.600 --> 05:13.830
- Thank you for playing.
- Ha, you're real funny.

05:13.860 --> 05:15.130
Man, I clobbered
that thing.

05:15.170 --> 05:17.130
I'm tellin' you,
these games are fixed.

05:17.170 --> 05:18.790
- Hello.
- How are you?

05:18.840 --> 05:20.770
Hi, what's your name?

05:20.800 --> 05:22.500
Step right up here.

05:22.540 --> 05:24.730
Over the hook, yeah.

05:26.910 --> 05:28.780
Whoa.

05:28.810 --> 05:31.840
- Who's this girl with Sara?
- Her name's Allie Hamilton.

05:31.880 --> 05:34.320
She's here for the summer
with her family.

05:34.350 --> 05:35.650
Dad's got more
money than God.

05:35.690 --> 05:37.780
- Hi, Fin!
- Hi, honey.

05:37.820 --> 05:40.620
Look, I won you a prize.

05:40.660 --> 05:43.990
Oh, Fin, thank you!

05:46.000 --> 05:48.400
- Oww!
- Yeah.

05:48.430 --> 05:50.190
Hey great, huh?

05:50.230 --> 05:52.060
Hey Allie, you want
some cotton candy?

05:52.100 --> 05:54.130
- Umm, okay.
- That would be so much fun.

05:55.970 --> 05:58.570
You only get
one chance, son.

05:58.610 --> 06:00.970
- You want to dance with me?
- No.

06:01.010 --> 06:04.140
- Why not?
- 'Cause I don't want to.

06:04.180 --> 06:07.170
Noah, she's with us.

06:07.220 --> 06:11.120
Hey Allie, you want
to ride the Ferris wheel?

06:11.150 --> 06:12.680
- I'd love to.
- All right.

06:12.720 --> 06:14.350
Excuse me.

06:15.630 --> 06:17.180
Excuse me.

06:21.260 --> 06:24.170
- Noah Calhoun.
- What?

06:24.200 --> 06:26.960
Works down at the lumber yard
with Fin.

06:27.000 --> 06:29.160
Oh...

06:29.210 --> 06:32.170
Did you see he was standing like
two inches away from my face?

06:32.210 --> 06:34.340
Yeah, I saw.
That's Noah, though.

06:36.050 --> 06:37.600
You know I'm surprised
he even came over.

06:37.650 --> 06:38.980
I think he likes you.

06:59.100 --> 07:00.800
Hey what... jerk...

07:00.840 --> 07:04.200
Get off me.
Don't touch me.

07:04.240 --> 07:06.300
- Hey!
- Well, I... ugh!

07:06.340 --> 07:08.330
- What are you doing?
- Hey, you can't do that!

07:08.380 --> 07:10.070
I'll pay you
when I get down, Tommy.

07:10.110 --> 07:11.910
I'm Noah Calhoun.

07:11.950 --> 07:14.040
- So?!
- So, it's really nice to meet you.

07:14.080 --> 07:16.640
- Allie, who is this guy?
- I don't know, Noah Calhoun.

07:16.690 --> 07:19.120
- I would really like to take you out.
- Friend! Do you mind?

07:20.860 --> 07:23.760
You can't sit more than two people
in a chair, Noah.

07:23.790 --> 07:25.260
Okay, Tommy,
all right.

07:28.300 --> 07:30.890
Get down, Noah,
you're gonna kill yourself!

07:30.930 --> 07:32.130
Noah, cut it out.

07:32.170 --> 07:33.830
Now, will you
go out with me?

07:33.870 --> 07:35.530
What?

07:35.570 --> 07:37.510
- No.
- No?

07:37.540 --> 07:38.870
- No.
- No?

07:38.910 --> 07:40.570
Hey pal,
she just told you.

07:40.610 --> 07:41.700
Why not?

07:41.750 --> 07:43.740
I don't know,
because I don't want to.

07:43.780 --> 07:44.800
Noah!

07:44.850 --> 07:47.180
What? Well, you leave me
no other choice then.

07:48.280 --> 07:49.410
Oh my God.

07:49.450 --> 07:50.440
I'm not kidding.

07:50.490 --> 07:52.220
- Noah, stop fooling around.
- What are you doing?

07:52.260 --> 07:54.660
- Noah, grab the bar.
- I'm gonna ask you one more time.

07:54.690 --> 07:56.280
Will you...

07:56.330 --> 07:59.060
- or will you not go out with me?
- Noah, you best come on.

07:59.100 --> 08:02.000
- God damn, my hand's slipping.
- Then grab the bar, you idiot.

08:02.030 --> 08:04.760
- Not until she agrees.
- Ah, go on out with him, honey.

08:04.800 --> 08:07.000
- Okay, okay, fine,
I'll go out with you.

08:07.040 --> 08:08.300
- What?
- No, don't do me any favors.

08:08.340 --> 08:09.670
No, no. I want to.

08:09.710 --> 08:11.040
- You want to? You want to?
- Yes!

08:11.070 --> 08:13.040
- Say it.
- I want to go out with you.

08:13.080 --> 08:15.670
- Say it again.
- I want to go out with you.

08:15.710 --> 08:18.040
All right, all right
we'll go out.

08:18.080 --> 08:20.850
You think
you're so smart, don't you?

08:20.880 --> 08:22.550
That wasn't funny,
Noah, you idiot!

08:22.590 --> 08:26.020
No, it's okay,
I'll take care of this.

08:26.060 --> 08:27.750
What are you doing?

08:27.790 --> 08:28.780
Please don't do that.

08:28.830 --> 08:30.350
Please don't do that, Allie.

08:30.390 --> 08:32.120
I can't believe...

08:32.160 --> 08:33.790
Oh God.

08:35.630 --> 08:37.400
You're not so cocky now,
are ya?

08:37.430 --> 08:39.300
I'm gonna get you for that.

08:39.340 --> 08:41.740
Ah, maybe you will,
maybe you won't.

08:44.310 --> 08:47.610
- Did he say anything to you?
- Oh, yeah, will you look at that?

08:47.640 --> 08:49.540
It's that girl from the Carnival,
right?

08:52.150 --> 08:54.050
Do you remember me?

08:54.080 --> 08:56.570
Yeah, sure,
Mr. Underwear, was it?

08:56.620 --> 08:58.350
- Well, I...
- How could I forget.

08:58.390 --> 08:59.880
Yeah, I wanted to clear
that up with you,

08:59.920 --> 09:01.410
because
I'm really sorry about that.

09:01.460 --> 09:02.750
It was a really stupid thing
to do...

09:02.790 --> 09:04.380
crawl up a Ferris wheel
to talk to somebody.

09:04.430 --> 09:06.330
But I had
to be next to you.

09:06.360 --> 09:08.520
I was being
drawn to you.

09:11.570 --> 09:14.000
Oh... oh, jeez,
what a line!

09:14.040 --> 09:16.400
You use that
on all the girls?

09:16.440 --> 09:18.170
- No.
- Right.

09:18.210 --> 09:20.510
I saw you the other night
with little Miss Ribbons.

09:20.540 --> 09:22.200
- What are you doing tonight?
- What?

09:22.250 --> 09:24.270
Or tomorrow night,
or this weekend, whatever.

09:24.310 --> 09:26.250
- Why?
- Why? Our date.

09:26.280 --> 09:27.540
What date?

09:27.580 --> 09:29.310
- The date that you agreed to.
- No...

09:29.350 --> 09:31.550
Yes, you did.
You promised and you swore it.

09:31.590 --> 09:33.350
Well, I guess
I changed my mind.

09:34.960 --> 09:37.320
Look, I know you get some dirty guy
coming up to you

09:37.360 --> 09:38.880
on the street...
you don't know him.

09:38.930 --> 09:40.760
You don't know me,
but I know me.

09:42.430 --> 09:44.160
And when I see something
that I like,

09:44.200 --> 09:46.530
I gotta ha...
I love it.

09:46.570 --> 09:48.630
I go... I mean,
I go crazy for it.

09:48.670 --> 09:51.440
Okay, what are you
talking about?

09:51.470 --> 09:52.670
Well, you.

09:53.840 --> 09:55.540
Oh, you're good.

09:55.580 --> 09:57.210
- What?
- You're good.

09:57.250 --> 09:59.720
- No. No, you're getting me wrong.
- You're good. You are.

09:59.750 --> 10:01.270
- You're fantastic.
- I'm not.

10:01.320 --> 10:03.180
You really are.
I'm impressed.

10:03.220 --> 10:06.520
- I'm not usually like this, I'm sorry.
- Oh, yes, you are.

10:06.560 --> 10:08.650
I can be fun,
if you want...

10:08.690 --> 10:12.180
pensive, uh, smart,

10:12.230 --> 10:14.960
uh, superstitious,
brave.

10:15.000 --> 10:17.930
And uh... I can be light on my feet.

10:17.970 --> 10:20.530
I could be
whatever you want.

10:20.570 --> 10:23.300
You just tell me what you want
and I'll be that for you.

10:24.440 --> 10:25.870
You're dumb.

10:28.140 --> 10:29.510
I could be that.

10:32.420 --> 10:34.410
Come on, one date.
What's it gonna hurt?

10:34.450 --> 10:36.110
Umm...
I don't think so.

10:36.150 --> 10:37.980
Well, what I can I do
to change your mind?

10:38.020 --> 10:39.960
Guess you'll figure
something out.

10:41.960 --> 10:44.430
- You sure she's coming?
- Relax, pal, it's all set up.

10:44.460 --> 10:45.980
We're meeting her
for the late show.

10:46.030 --> 10:47.860
Look... what did
I tell you? Come on.

10:53.500 --> 10:56.940
Oh my goodness,
what a coincidence!

10:56.970 --> 10:58.700
I need to talk to you
for a second.

10:58.740 --> 11:02.510
- He's here!
- Allie, you remember Noah, don't you?

11:02.550 --> 11:03.530
- Yes, I remember.
- Yeah.

11:03.580 --> 11:05.510
- Come here.
- Fin!

11:05.550 --> 11:07.210
- Hi.
- Hi.

11:07.250 --> 11:09.580
- It's nice to see you again.
- You too.

11:09.620 --> 11:11.780
- You look great.
- Aw, thanks.

11:11.820 --> 11:13.520
Really, really great.

11:13.560 --> 11:15.250
You do look great.
You look great.

11:15.290 --> 11:18.690
And I know I look great,
so could we please go see this movie?

11:18.730 --> 11:21.490
- The show's about to start.
- After you.

11:21.530 --> 11:24.160
You come back here,
Li'I Abner.

11:24.200 --> 11:26.760
You ain't gonna catch me,
Daisy Mae!

11:26.800 --> 11:29.070
It's Sadie Hawkins Day,
I'm supposed to catch you!

11:29.110 --> 11:30.830
I'm faster than you.

11:32.840 --> 11:34.610
No, No!

11:34.640 --> 11:36.840
I'll get you!

11:38.010 --> 11:39.950
I'm going get...

11:39.980 --> 11:41.450
Here I come!

11:41.480 --> 11:43.980
You better run fast!

11:53.600 --> 11:55.590
You ketchum Polecat
far and squar.

12:01.870 --> 12:04.530
Wait for me.

12:04.570 --> 12:06.600
What happened
in that movie?

12:07.940 --> 12:10.110
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

12:11.580 --> 12:13.710
- What are you guys doing?
- Want to walk with me?

12:13.750 --> 12:14.740
Yeah, what's going on?

12:14.780 --> 12:16.220
- Yeah.
- We're gonna walk.

12:16.250 --> 12:18.740
Do you guys
love each other?

12:18.790 --> 12:21.090
Huh?
Oh, I get it.

12:21.120 --> 12:23.920
- You guys do love each other.
- Don't do anything I wouldn't do.

12:23.960 --> 12:25.050
Okay, good bye.

12:25.090 --> 12:27.590
- All right, all right.
- Mmm...

12:31.670 --> 12:33.730
That was fun.

12:33.770 --> 12:35.640
Mm-hmm.

12:35.670 --> 12:38.070
I haven't seen a movie
in ages.

12:38.110 --> 12:39.870
- Really?
- Huh-uh.

12:39.910 --> 12:42.710
Not since
I was a little kid.

12:42.750 --> 12:44.340
What?

12:44.380 --> 12:46.180
No, I, uh...

12:46.220 --> 12:48.810
I'm busy, you know,
I don't have a lot of time.

12:50.120 --> 12:51.550
- You're busy?
- Mm-hmm.

12:51.590 --> 12:55.180
I have a very
strict schedule.

12:55.220 --> 12:56.990
My days are all
planned out.

12:57.030 --> 13:01.260
I get up in the morning... breakfast,
math tutor, Latin tutor, lunch,

13:01.300 --> 13:05.030
tennis lessons, dance lessons...
sometimes both...

13:05.070 --> 13:08.900
French tutor, piano lesson,
then I eat dinner.

13:08.940 --> 13:10.930
And after dinner
I spend time with my family.

13:10.970 --> 13:13.770
And then l... I catch up
on some reading.

13:16.850 --> 13:18.280
Wow.

13:19.450 --> 13:21.250
Sounds like the road
to success.

13:21.280 --> 13:22.950
Oh, you bet.

13:22.990 --> 13:24.650
We're applying
to all these colleges...

13:24.690 --> 13:29.150
umm... Radcliffe, Sarah Lawrence...
those are the ones we want.

13:30.830 --> 13:33.730
- And who's we?
- What?

13:33.760 --> 13:35.860
You just said,
"The ones that we want."

13:35.900 --> 13:37.560
Oh, Mom and Daddy.

13:37.600 --> 13:39.400
We decide
everything together.

13:40.770 --> 13:42.970
Everything?

13:43.010 --> 13:44.670
No, not everything.

13:44.710 --> 13:46.440
But the important
things, yes.

13:48.040 --> 13:51.280
And then everything else,
you get to decide all by yourself?

13:53.120 --> 13:55.980
- Don't be rude.
- I'm sorry.

13:58.550 --> 14:01.610
Just trying to figure out
what you do for fun.

14:01.660 --> 14:04.520
What do you mean?

14:04.560 --> 14:06.930
I mean...

14:06.960 --> 14:08.560
I don't know,
I mean all those things

14:08.600 --> 14:11.160
are things you
have to do, right?

14:11.200 --> 14:15.070
So what do you do
because you want to?

14:15.100 --> 14:17.230
I just told ya.

14:20.310 --> 14:21.970
I don't know.

14:22.010 --> 14:24.500
This surprises me.

14:24.550 --> 14:25.840
Why?

14:25.880 --> 14:29.340
I just always figured
you were kinda...

14:29.390 --> 14:31.180
Kinda what?

14:31.220 --> 14:32.520
Just...

14:34.560 --> 14:37.390
- Free.
- What?

14:37.430 --> 14:38.950
Free.

14:41.230 --> 14:43.760
I am free.

14:43.800 --> 14:46.560
You don't seem like it.

14:46.600 --> 14:48.570
Well, I am.

14:50.710 --> 14:52.700
Come here,
I want to show you something.

14:52.740 --> 14:56.410
- Noah, what are you doing?
- Just come on.

14:56.450 --> 14:59.880
- You're gonna get run over.
- By all the cars?

15:07.660 --> 15:09.250
My Dad and I used
to come out here

15:09.290 --> 15:13.020
and lay down and watch
the lights change.

15:13.060 --> 15:16.050
And watch them go
from green to red to yellow.

15:17.700 --> 15:20.460
You could try it,
if you wanted to.

15:20.500 --> 15:22.900
- No.
- Why not?

15:22.940 --> 15:25.700
Because I don't know...
will you just get up?

15:25.740 --> 15:28.140
That's your problem,
you know that?

15:29.480 --> 15:31.000
You don't do
what you want.

15:39.420 --> 15:40.950
Okay.

15:58.170 --> 16:00.140
What happens
if a car comes?

16:00.180 --> 16:01.870
- We die.
- What?

16:01.910 --> 16:03.850
Just relax.
Just trust.

16:03.880 --> 16:06.310
You need to learn
how to trust.

16:08.020 --> 16:09.480
Okay.

16:12.560 --> 16:14.280
- Painting.
- Hmm?

16:14.320 --> 16:16.880
You asked me
what I do for me.

16:16.930 --> 16:20.660
- What now?
- I love to paint.

16:20.700 --> 16:23.890
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

16:23.930 --> 16:25.990
Huh.

16:26.040 --> 16:29.970
Most of the time, I have all these
thoughts bouncing around in my head.

16:30.010 --> 16:33.310
But with a brush
in my hand,

16:33.340 --> 16:36.110
the world just gets
kinda quiet.

16:44.190 --> 16:45.850
Get out of the street!

16:54.700 --> 16:55.720
Are you okay?

16:58.430 --> 17:00.530
Why are you laughing?

17:03.840 --> 17:06.270
Oh, that was fun.

17:10.680 --> 17:12.380
Do you want
to dance with me?

17:14.080 --> 17:15.110
Sure.

17:18.090 --> 17:19.650
- Now?
- Mm-hmm.

17:19.690 --> 17:21.320
- Here?
- Mm-hmm.

17:21.360 --> 17:23.950
Not supposed to dance
in the middle of the street.

17:23.990 --> 17:27.090
Who said dance
in the street?

17:27.130 --> 17:28.760
And we don't
have any music.

17:28.800 --> 17:31.270
Well,
we'll make some.

